article.description: Darnell Edge had a career-high 32 points as Fairleigh Dickinson topped Bryant 97-84 on Saturday.
article.headline: Edge lifts Fairleigh Dickinson over Bryant 97-84
article.linkText: Edge lifts Fairleigh Dickinson over Bryant 97-84
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Darnell Edge had a career-high 32 points as Fairleigh Dickinson topped Bryant 97-84 on Saturday. Edge made 11 of 14 shots, including 7 of 8 on 3-pointers. Jahlil Jenkins had 18 points, seven assists and five steals for Fairleigh Dickinson (13-13, 8-6 Northeast Conference). Xzavier Malone-Key added 15 points. Elyjah Williams had 12 points and eight rebounds for the home team. Mike Holloway Jr. had nine points and 10 rebounds. Only four players had rebounds for the Knights. Adam Grant had 27 points for the Bulldogs (8-17, 5-9), who have now lost five consecutive games. He also had seven turnovers but only two assists. Sabastian Townes added 23 points. Joe Kasperzyk had 14 points. The Knights improved to 2-0 against the Bulldogs this season. Fairleigh Dickinson defeated Bryant 78-63 on Jan. 26. Fairleigh Dickinson plays Sacred Heart at home on Thursday. Bryant matches up against Wagner at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
